Content: Pro traders arent any better at predicting where the market will go than a hobby trader and its not the job. The difference is all in execution Finding lvls protecting profits once available stopping out  adjusting when wrong and consistant loss size control. Focus there

So far the COSM chart was absolute carbon copy regardless if your opinion whether you agree or not. The chart I posted early ended up being 4 cents off.  23.80 was todays high GLMD so far  and the COSM chart the HOD was 23.84.  So not going to sit here and debate if it was a good comparison or not we already got that answer by the stock itself.   Either way  similarities here on COSM and GLMD is fear of selling or in todays case the fear of covering in this case.   COSM had fear that the trade would be broken  HOOD ended up getting caught upside down losing 50 million  Like COSM likewise we had the fear of covering your shares on GLMD today because most brokers that abide by FINRA rules you cannot recycle the shares. Once you cover you have to re locate the stock. And the price was now .50share instead of .02 this AM. Yes some brokers allow you to recycle for now.  Also on the way that it went up from 81011 etc. was slow enough to keep shorts in w out forcing them out margin wise while forcing them to build into a position before each stuff move.  As we pointed out at @IUTraders each stuff move was IMMEDIATELY soaked.    THIS IS THE NEW TRAP    Right now theyre just collecting into 19.40s as I write this.  Anyway  then they put the jets on.   Couple that with guys afraid to take proper risk management due to fear of no more locates or unwillingness to pay .501share and here we are.  They also know coming off the recent TNON move that NO ONE will have balls to swing short over night if they create enough fear into close no matter what they soak today they can sell into the final few minutes andor AHs if they get stuck. They have upper hand today but I truly believe most of the bias today on short side was there because they feared not being able to get back in and re locate.   Best of luck  high risk trade. Be careful and trade em well.
Im happy with somewhere in between lol  have locked in a chunk so far

Just that regular reminder in case you need to hear it  ... there have been so many dumpers on the China walk up plays lately  people get FOMO and forget the risk associated with them.   Traders fail to look at the volume and short first and ask questions later.   Think back to the warning on Sunday video the day before ZJYL because the FOMO from missing CHSN.   Once again all it takes is one.   Its not worth it.   It can make or break your career on short side w out real liquidity present thats why I made that point earlier if you like those odds  go for it. Not for me.
